National Security Advisor Susan E. Rice spoke with Indian National Security Advisor Ajit Doval to condemn the cross-border attack on the Indian Army Brigade headquarters in Uri and offer condolences to the victims. Rice affirmed President Obama's commitment to bringing the perpetrators of terrorism to justice and highlighted the danger of cross-border terrorism. She reiterated the expectation for Pakistan to take effective action against designated terrorist individuals and entities. Rice also discussed the shared commitment with India to pursuing peace and regional stability and pledged to deepen collaboration on counterterrorism matters.